The draw for the FA semi-final have been conducted on Sunday. Gary Lineker and Dion Dublin took charge of the event during half of Leicester City vs Manchester United. Leicester went on to beat United 3-1 at the King Power Stadium. Kelechi Iheanacho scored twice, while Youri Tielemans also got on the scoresheet for Brendan Rodgers’ men. Mason Greenwood scored for United, but it was ultimately not enough and Ole Gunnar Solskjaer will now focus on winning the Europa League. Leicester will now face Southampton in the last four. The Saints beat Bournemouth 3-0 yesterday. Chelsea will take on Premier League leaders Manchester City in the other semi-final. The Blues saw off Sheffield United 2-0 in Sunday’s early kick-off, while City beat Everton 2-0 on Saturday. Both matches will be played at Wembley on the weekend of April 17. The sides are playing for the right to take part in the 2021 final at Wembley on May 15.